{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1fd30069-ab04-4754-9893-e4141f237185","content":"**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** It works in a safe context just like any other unmanaged type:\n\n```csharp\nSpan<nint> signed = stackalloc nint[4];\nSpan<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];\n```\n\nOn this 64-bit system, `nint` is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size varies by platform), but you can use `nint.Size` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c108d1d1-6f47-4c9b-911c-8bbc289ca07c","outputTokens":149,"requestId":"1444:1B7339:12AC343:14EFF2F:6A0279A4"},"id":"45e9eb24-fe6c-457f-9d1a-f108357863a9","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:53.329Z","parentId":"7aa3e75b-002e-4d0d-8f17-3569587da82e"}
